deck_excerpt: Dragonmaids, but also your monsters are my materials
deck_description: This is a versatile deck featuring Fallen of Albaz as the star of the show. Dragonmaids are used as an all around good engine, but also to disguise what the deck is capable of. If the opponent uses their disruption on the Dragonmaids, they are more vulnerable to a Fallen of Albaz.  On a Dragonmaid start, the deck may play like a typical Dragonmaid deck and end the turn on a Sheou. It is also capable of linking up to Accesscode Talker and bringing out a Borreload Savage Dragon later.  On a Windwitch start, the turn ends on a Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon. From here there's a fun detour to take if you have your single copy of Magicalized Fusion, where you can bring out one of the spellcaster link monsters in order to summon Quintet Magician. He's nothing crazy, but the fact that he can't be Kaiju'd or fusioned away makes me happy.  On a start where you have access to Fallen of Albaz, you just feel out how the opponent will try to disrupt you, bait it out if you can, and then fusion their best monster away with Albion the Branded Dragon, Starving Venom Fusion Dragon, or Mudragon of the Swamp. Super Polymerization will also allow you to summon Albaz and then use Sprind the Irondash Dragon on your opponent's turn to use any one of the opponent's effect monsters as fusion material.

deck_excerpt: A deck focused on the power of Trickstars
deck_description: This deck uses Candina to search either Trickstar lightstage, Trickstar Festival, or Lycoris to then use lightstage to search either Mandrake, Lilybell, or Lycoris. Mandrake is there as fodder. Nightshade is there for 1 off plays if you have nothing in your hand. The traps mainly help Lycoris to deal a ton of dmg. The main play is to get Holly angle to an extra monster zone and get Band sweet guitar & Divardis to a zone that Holly angle points too.

deck_name: An Actual Mayakashi Deck (Zombies, but fun!) v2.0
deck_excerpt: Tired of boring meta decks? Sick to the stomach after playing against Eldlich? Then this might be THE zombie deck for you...
deck_description: Mayakashi is my favorite archetype, so seeing decks listed as "Mayakashi" decks with loads of other non-Mayakashi cards in them drives me up a wall. Mayakashis don't need to be paired up with other archetypes like Shiranui or Eldlich (*vomits*) to be good, they can whoop ass all on their own - and here's my deck to prove that. Pretty much every card in this deck is all about helping you combo into your big Mayakashi boss monsters. Will update this deck over time especially when those Mayakashi support cards come over from the OCG to the TCG. -Leo v2.0 Changes  I added a side deck! This strays a bit away from pure Mayakashi bc it involves putting some Danger! cards into the deck. Replace the Uni-Zombies and 1 Dakki if you want to slot the dangers in, and swap the Sunsaga for the Skillsaga. Dangers work pretty great with Mayakashi- they aren't held back by the summoning restrictions, and make your opponent send cards to your GY for absolutely free. Also in the side deck are two copies of Solemn Strike, just in case you need extra negates.

deck_excerpt: A Trap deck that Halfs your life for powerful effects.
deck_description:
Dinomorphia aka The Half Deck is a deck that will half your life for powerful Trap cards and Monster Effects.  First the Main Deck.  It is a control deck that is highly corrosive and able to grind for time if needed. The Monsters The main monster in the deck is Dinomorphia Therizia which sets any Dinomorphia trap from deck to the field.  In which you would set Dinomorphia Frenzy and if you already have Frenzy or Domain(Another less powerful Frenzy) you can set any trap needed according to the current game state.  The other Main Deck monster, Dinomorphia Diplos which sends a Dinomorphia trap to the grave to be used for their second effects, be able to recycle itself and Therizia, and or be used with Kentregina.  Both cards float upon destruction by banishing a any trap from GY.  Now the supporting cards.
  • Lord of the Heavenly Prison - To protect your traps and to help set up for next turn if SS(Both it and Ultimate Conductor can be used for an xyz monster)
  • Miscellaneousaurus - To ensure the activation of your Main Monsters
  • Ultimate Conductor Tyranno - A great last resort and Boss Monster if all else goes wrong(Both it and Heavenly Prison can be used for an xyz monster)
  • Flowerdino - An extender and a way to recycle traps and get an extra Special Summon
The Spells There are very few spells and great alternative spells that can be included.  Fossil Dig is a great way to search your Dinomorphia Monsters and if you already have one, to search Misc to ensure they cant be negated.  Pot of Extravagance to draw cards and set up for your opponents turn.  Then Called By the Grave because in a format with loads of Handtraps you need to be able to stop them.  Great alternatives and inclusions are
  • Pot of Prosperity(Other good draw card)
  • Pot of Duality(Also a good draw card)
The Traps Dinomorphia is a heavily Trap reliant deck to be able to control the game.  Cards like Dinomorphia Frenzy and Dinomorphia Domain.  Frenzy is to make Rexstrum and Domain to Make Kentregina and then use its effect to make Rexstrum.  Dinomorphia Brute, which is a non-targeting destruction that destroys your Dinomorphia and one card on their field(Which Dinomorphia is the easy winner cause it can float endlessly)  Dinomorphia Shell, which is a way to stop your opponent from attacking a low Atk Kentregina or Rexstrum by having the opponent have to attack it first.  Also it can be used in pair with Brute for a destruction(Though there wont be a floating effect).  Dinomorphia Sonic, which is just a Spell/Trap negate and destruction.  Lastly Dinomorphia Alert, which Special Summons two Dinomorphia monsters from your GY.  As well, all Dinomorphia Traps have a secondary effect to stop a dangerous situation with burn and attack damage.  Shell and Sonic for Battle damage, and Domain, Frenzy, Brute, and Alert for Effect damage.  Other traps include.
  • The Solemn cards, which lessens your life more for more negates
  • Hope for Escape, which is a great card for drawing more cards later in the game when your life is extremely low
  • Skill Drain, oppressive floodgate that lowers your life by 1000
  • Ferret Flames, a great card that bounces all monsters from the field until the combined attack is less then your life point(aka all of them later in the round)
Extra Deck The Extra Deck is the place everyone will be different because there are so many diverse and good ways to make it, but everyone can agree that three Dinomorphia Rexstrum and Dinomorphia Kentregina is mandatory.  Rexsturm is the best card in the deck and is your main card to get out.  Rexsturm is a walking Skill Drain on legs that hits like a small planet(Hehe Hope for Escape planet joke ahahahahahahaha).  All monsters with less or equal attack to your life points are negated on the field, so DPE and Dragoon are useless and just there.  To help be able to use the effect, it has a second effect to half your life to make the attack of all monsters on the field equal to your life which can be used to otk and or to negate the entire field.  Dinomorphia Kentregina is a monster that halfs your life to imitate a trap in the GY by banishing it.  It has a base attack of 4000, but it never will have 4000 attack.  How it works is that it loses attack up to your life points, so if you have 4000 Life points it has 0 attack, 2000 Life points it has 2000 attack, and so on.  Dinomorphia Stealthbergia, which makes it so if your Life points are under 2000 trap cards that cost life no longer cost life to use, so Solem Strike and Skill Drain can be activated even if you dont have enough Life points to activate it.  Stealthbergia can be at any card limit, but two is the most reasonable in my opinion.  The rest of the Extra deck is heavily customizable.  In my list the Extra Deck monster are.
  • Evolzar  Dolkka, which is a great Monster negate and destruction.
  • Evolzar Laggia, which is a great Spell negate and destruction.
  • Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Gustav Max, which is a way to get game(EVERYONE WOULD KNOW IT WAS A JOKE.  COWBOY FOR GAME IS FOR THE PAST, WE ALL KNOW STALLING FOR TIME AND GUSTAV FOR GAME IS THE NEW ERA).
  • Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Juggernaut Liebe, a big monster to put on Gustav Max for otks.
  • Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder, a way to just wipe boards after attacking with any of the xyz monsters
  • Knightmare Phoenix, a Spell/Trap removal cause you could never have enough removal cards.
Yet just cause I use these cards doesnt mean you have too.  Other great Extra deck Monsters include
  • Abyss Dweller
  • Diagusto Emeral
  • Number 101: Silent Honor ARK
  • Tornado Dragon
  • Number 35: Ravenous Tarantula
  • Number 81: Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Super Dora
There is probably more but those are the ones I considered the most when deck building. For all those who did read this Thank you and I hope you have as much fun with this deck as I will.  If you wanna support me I have a Twitch and YouTube and I might start streaming regularly and post Deck profiles and other fun videos.

deck_name: Laval in Master Duel, is it worth it
deck_excerpt: Pain
deck_description:
Laval is a archetype that is able to play an absolutely ridiculous hyper combo strategy that is pretty similar to synchron, but is much more bricky. It’s an old archetype originating from the synchro era, and it shows, the cards in this deck are very poorly written in both a good way and a bad way.

It’s also a big archetype, meaning it has its own pack, meaning that more of its better cards are supers and ultras, meaning it’s hard to make.

I’ll be replacing sulfer divine with shooting quasar when I get it.

But I, being me, have decided to suffer to make this deck so you don’t have to. And so I did, here’s my list.

Is it worth the amount of resources it requires to make this? No. It isn’t worth it at all.

Feel free to ask me any questions below and I’ll answer to the best of my ability.

deck_excerpt: Rouge Deck to frustrate Master Duel Meta by basically locking up their field
deck_description:
• The main strategy is to bring out either Pachycephalo, Vanitys Fiend or a Barrier Statue (you can change them however you like)
  • Block spell or trap effects with Denko
  • Equip them so they are stronger than any generic level 4
  • Watch your opponents quiver in fear as they are locked out of doing anything
  • You can throw in Vanity's Emptiness if you think it's more consistent
  • The Extra Deck can just be any kind of random Link Monster
 
  • Weaknesses:
    •  Monarchs
    • Spells and (Hand-)Traps
 
  • Any ways I could improve this deck? Let me know in the comments!

deck_excerpt: Invoked Dogmatika dpe with Crossout Designator
deck_description: I have 2 ash and 2 droll because i don't like having hand traps x3 that can be used once per turn.  I play 1 invocation because the first game i need 1 invocation only, i would add second invocation for the 2nd and 3rd game but because i main crossout designator really i don't need second invocation.  I main lightning storm because for me the most important turn is my first turn ,doesn't matter if i go second or first,  even if i draw lightning storm other turn i can just use it as material for mechaba  Some players would consider adding Small World but i don't use it, i think 18 starters  for creating a board is enough and i don't need more than that.

deck_excerpt: Lol imagine pendulums playing too defensively
deck_description: Can be played as a mixed aggressive and control. Recycles spells and basically has infinite counter supply.  Servant of Endymion - Can bring out your negates by using 3 spell counters.  Endymion, the Mighty Master of Magic - can basically wipe a field with it's pendulum effect by removing 6 counters. While it's a monster, it's untargetable, and can negate spell/traps  Beast King Jackal - Able to negate monster effects  Master Cerebus - Can search out Jackal and banish opponents monsters. Cannot be destroyed by card effects with 4 or more counters.  Spring of Mysterune - One of the most important card of the decks allowing you to draw 3 cards every turn and activate quick-play spells from your hand.  Point of Mysterune - Searches your cards and banishes your opponents top deck  Munnin - Searches deceit and can be used for link plays, can be used for health gain too  Geri - Recycles field spell and deceit. Also used for link plays or can be used defensively or to destroy monsters  Deck Goal:  Deck out opponent (agressive)  Build up counters and obliterate opponent(control)  -Always keep 1 quick-play spell in your hand if you already used your field spells effect unless in certain situations. You can then use your field spell to recycle more cards and get more quick-play spells on your opponents turn.  -If you plan on going agressive, you still have to play control. It's best to keep your quick-play spells in your hand if you are going this route. This way you can negate with your monsters on board and use your spells when you need them. Works best if your opponent is low on cards and you wiped their field.  -Will always loose to imperial order and has a very tough time against Flundereeze
